1 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the DOTD shall organize and conduct no less
2 than two public forums with affected residents and business owners to gather feedback and
3 insight regarding the impacts of the recent recurring flooding along the corridor.
4 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the DOTD shall incorporate the input, expertise,
5 and support of relevant local municipal entities, including but not limited to the Shreveport
6 Public Works Department, the Shreveport Department of Operational Services, Office of
7 Water and Sewerage, and Shreveport Traffic Engineering.
8 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the DOTD shall submit a written report detailing
9 its findings and recommendations, including proposed plans to mitigate the flooding during
10 rain events, to the joint transportation, highways, and public works committee at least sixty
11 days prior to the convening of the 2027 Regular Session.
12 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the DOTD shall submit a copy of the report to
13 the state representative for Louisiana House District No. 2 and the state senator for Louisiana
14 Senate District No. 39 at least sixty days prior to the convening of the 2027 Regular Session.
15 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of the Resolution be transmitted to the
16 secretary of the DOTD.
